headline: US Stock Market Today S&P 500 Futures Edge Higher As Rate Tension Builds
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Thursday, Jan, 29 2026 US stock futures are pointing higher this morning, with E-mini S&P 500 contracts up about 0.25% and Nasdaq-100 futures ahead by roughly 0.3%, as investors weigh firm bond yields against easier global rate signals. The US 10 year Treasury yield is holding near 4.25% to 4.3%, which keeps borrowing costs elevated for mortgages and many businesses.
